\‘How,’ said Demetrius, ‘have you accomplished so long a journey in
so small a fraction of the day?’ And Apollonius replied： ‘Imagine what
you will, flying ram or wings of wax excepted, so long as you ascribe it to
the intervention of a divine escort.'
